# Section comments

When adding or editing Python in this repo, group logical blocks with section headers so workshop participants can scan the file.

## Format

```python
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Section title (short noun phrase)
# One or two sentences: what this block does and why it exists.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
def my_function():
    ...
```

## When to add sections

- Public entry points vs internal helpers
- Setup/bootstrap vs runtime logic
- Parsing/normalization vs side effects (I/O, network)
- Graph construction vs node handlers
- Observability (logging, OTel, callbacks) vs business logic

## Guidelines

- Prefer section headers over line-by-line comments.
- Keep explanations plain English; name the consumer when helpful (e.g. "CLI and Slack call this").
- Do not restate obvious code (`i += 1  # increment i`).
- Match existing section style in neighboring files.
- No blank line between the closing `# ---` line and the code below it.
